<TITLE> 4 die, 50 down with diarrhoea in Chandpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, May 8 (bdnews24.com)Four people have died of diarrhoea and at least 50 others infected with the illness in last three days in a Chandpur village, a hospital spokesperson said on Friday. The diarrhoea onslaught is aging through Ugharia of Chitoshi West Upazila in Sharrasti, Chandpur. Dr Abdul Mannan, Shahrasti Upazila health and family planning officer, told bdnews24.com Marjahan, 3, daughter of Mujib, Selina Begum, 24, wife of Kamal Hossain, Jainab Banu, 80, wife of late Abdur Rashid, and Abul Kashem, 80, have died of diarrhoea. The others are being treated in Matlab Diarrhoea Hospital in Chandpur, ICDDR'B Hospital in Dhaka and some other hospitals, family sources said. "A three-member mobile medical team led by heath assistant Masudur Rahman Bhuiyan has started working to tackle the situation," Dr Mannan said. UP chairman of West Chitoshi Md Anwar Hossain told bdnews24.com a lack of sanitation, use of polluted water, and health unawareness are causing diarrhoea in Ugharia and nearby villages. He said health officials distributed oral saline among the patients. bdnews2
